Uses of Package
com.kuka.geometry

  • Packages that use com.kuka.geometry 
    Package Description
    com.kuka.device.common
    This package contains common device related interfaces and classes.
    com.kuka.functional
    Package contains functional programming aspects.
    com.kuka.geometry
    This package contains interfaces and classes for the KUKA scene graph and geometry model.
    com.kuka.geometry.connections
    This package contains interfaces and classes describing connections between Frames.
    com.kuka.geometry.events
    Contains classes of the KUKA scene graph event model.
    com.kuka.geometry.internal
    Contains internal classes of the KUKA geometry model.
    com.kuka.geometry.shapes
    This package contains classes for usage of geometrical shapes within the KUKA geometry model.
    com.kuka.geometry.templates
    This package contains classes for usage of templates within the KUKA geometry model.
    com.kuka.motion
    This package contains interfaces and classes for the KUKA motion model.
    com.kuka.objectparameters
    Contains interfaces for the runtime representation of object parameters.
    com.kuka.scenegraph
    This package contains interfaces which declare geometric capabilities.

    Class and Description
    Frame
    A frame represents a coordinate system in three-dimensional space.

    Represents a directed path (i.e. frame chain) between two frames connected through the frame tree.
    FrameChainElement
    A single frame chain element in the directed path from source to target frame.
    IObjectEventProvider
    Provides methods for adding or removing listeners for the event model.
    IRedundancyCollection
    Interface for holding redundancy information.
    IRobotFlange

    ObjectConnection
    Represents the connection between two spatial objects.
    ObjectFrame
    Represents a frame that belongs to a SpatialObject.
    PhysicalObject

    Shape
    Base class for every shape.
    SpatialObject
    Represents a geometric object that may be part of a scene graph.
    VirtualObject
    Represents a virtual object that may be part of a scene graph.
    World
    Spatial object representing World.
    World.IValidationDelegate
    An World.IValidationDelegate is given the opportunity to prevent changes to SpatialObjects before they happen.
